# Andrew smokes once — when the feature is DONE

**Ratified Andrew 2026-06-23.** Agents take a feature **spec → completion** with full Playwright coverage. Andrew enters **once**, when the feature is **DONE**, for quirks / real hardware / human judgment — **not** to re-prove regressions.

## Division of labor

| Owner | Responsibility |
|-------|----------------|
| **Agents** | Implement spec; **Playwright test per behavioral/visual acceptance item** ([`playwright-on-fix.mdc`](playwright-on-fix.mdc)); green automated gates ([`test-selection.mdc`](test-selection.mdc)); author smokebook **before** requesting Andrew — but Andrew does **not** run it until DONE. |
| **Andrew** | **One** hardware smoke per feature when DONE: subjective UX, real devices/browsers, external apps (Teams, iOS Safari), `PLAYWRIGHT-GAP` items. **Not** regression re-proof. |

## Feature DONE (orchestrator verifies before requesting Andrew smoke)

All must be true:

1. **Scope complete** — every in-spec acceptance item implemented (no hidden "follow-up" blockers).
2. **Playwright mapped** — each behavioral/visual item has a named `wb-regression` test (file + title), or explicit `PLAYWRIGHT-GAP` + [`docs/BACKLOG.md`](../../docs/BACKLOG.md) entry.
3. **Agent gates green** — merge-tier suite passed (`test:wb-affected:run` minimum; `test:wb-sync` when WB/sync in scope or merging to integration/`master`).
4. **Smokebook ready** — follows [`SMOKEBOOK-TEMPLATE.md`](../../docs/handoff/SMOKEBOOK-TEMPLATE.md); items are **new surface + human judgment only** (see below).
5. **Preview verified** — Vercel `branchAlias` fetched (never guessed); branch pushed.

Until all five pass: **do not ask Andrew to smoke.**

## Smokebook scope (what Andrew's run is for)

**Include:** novel UX, feel, hardware-only paths, visual polish judgment, cross-device layout, pilot-realistic flows Playwright cannot hermeticize.

**Exclude / mark explicitly:** anything already covered by Playwright — tag items in Notes as `[automated: <spec> › <test title>]` and treat as **N/A with notes** ("covered by Playwright gate") unless a **human-only** reason exists (e.g. "Teams desktop WebRTC feel").

**Forbidden smokebook patterns:**

- Per-fix or mid-wave "please smoke this commit"
- Items that duplicate `@wb-*` tests without `[human-only: …]` justification
- Using Andrew smoke as the **first** regression net for behavior Playwright could catch

## Anti-patterns (process failures)

- Andrew smoked the same regression twice → we failed [`playwright-on-fix.mdc`](playwright-on-fix.mdc).
- Andrew asked to smoke before DONE checklist → orchestrator jumped the queue.
- Bug found in smoke that Playwright should have caught → add test **before** calling fix done; Andrew does not re-smoke that class again.

## Orchestrator one-liner for Andrew

> "Feature DONE — gates green, Playwright mapped. Smokebook is for **new UX + hardware judgment only**. Please smoke once."
